{
  "texts": [
    "(2) Effectiveness: The attention mechanism facilitates dynamic spatial interactions between tokens, contingent on the input itself.",
    "This section provides a brief overview of the evolution of backbone networks in foundation models, highlighting the transition from LSTMs to Transformers, followed by vision language model backbones from Convolutional neural networks (CNNs) [31] to Vision Transformers (ViTs) [32].Backbone Networks in Texts.",
    "Transformer has become the backbone of most pretrained language models, such as BERT [33], GPT [1], and T5 [34], building upon self-attention module and feed-forward networks (FFNs).",
    "The self-attention module facilitates token interaction, while FFN refines token representations using non-linear transformations.",
    "The Transformer architecture is designed to process tokens efficiently in parallel, thanks to the elimination of recurrent units and the use of position embeddings."
  ]
}